			 sys.all_columns (Transact-SQL) 

					 
								 03/14/2017 
							 2 minutes to read 
							 
								 Contributors 
								 
											 
								 

					 In this article 
						 THIS TOPIC APPLIES TO:   SQL Server (starting with 2008) Azure SQL Database Azure SQL Data Warehouse  Parallel Data Warehouse    Shows the union of all columns belonging to user-defined objects and system objects.   
 Column name 
 Data type 
 Description 
 object_id 
 int 
 ID of the object to which this column belongs. 
 name 
 sysname 
 Name of the column. Is unique within the object. 
 column_id 
 int 
 ID of the column. Is unique within the object.  Column IDs might not be sequential. 
 system_type_id 
 tinyint 
 ID of the system-type of the column. 
 user_type_id 
 int 
 ID of the type of the column as defined by the user.  To return the name of the type, join to the  sys.types  catalog view on t